#: ../../../usage/cli.md:1
msgid "The Pyodide Python CLI"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:3
msgid ""
"Pyodide includes a python CLI command which is a drop in replacement for the "
"native python CLI. For example all the following should work as expected:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:5
msgid ""
"python -c \"some command\"\n"
"python file.py\n"
"python -m some.module\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:10
msgid ""
"This is primarily useful for testing and experimentation. It can also be "
"helpful to install Pyodide Python packages using uv or pip for bundling "
"purposes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:13
msgid ""
"Execution is not sandboxed, this Pyodide Python has direct access to the "
"native file system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:16
msgid "Platform support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:18
msgid ""
"It should work on Linux and macOS. There is currently no Windows support. It "
"requires an installation of NodeJS >= 20."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:21
msgid "Installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:23
msgid "There are three ways to install the Pyodide CLI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:26
msgid "Github releases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:28
msgid ""
"You can download `pyodide-core-vv.vv.vv.tar.bz2` from github releases and "
"extract it. It contains the `python` command inside."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:31
msgid "Pyodide venv"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:33
msgid ""
"You can install `pyodide-build` with pip or uv and then run `pyodide venv ."
"venv-pyodide`. If you use uv to install `pyodide-build` make sure you run "
"`uv pip install pip`, it will not work without pip installed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:37
msgid "uv"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:39
msgid ""
"You can use `uv python install cpython-3.14.2-emscripten-wasm32-musl` to "
"install Pyodide. Then you can create a Pyodide venv with"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:41
msgid "uv venv .venv-pyodide -p cpython-3.14.2-emscripten-wasm32-musl\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:44
msgid "When you install packages you should use:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:45
msgid ""
"uv pip install --no-build --extra-index-url https://index.pyodide."
"org/314.0.0/ --index-strategy unsafe-best-match\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:49
msgid ""
"You can set these settings by default by putting the following in `uv.toml`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:50
msgid ""
"no-build = true\n"
"index-strategy = \"unsafe-best-match\"\n"
"\n"
"[[index]]\n"
"url = \"https://index.pyodide.org/314.0.0/\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:57
msgid "Or the following in `pyproject.toml`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:58
msgid ""
"tool.uv.no-build = true\n"
"tool.uv.index-strategy = \"unsafe-best-match\"\n"
"\n"
"[[tool.uv.index]]\n"
"url = \"https://index.pyodide.org/314.0.0/\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/cli.md:65
msgid ""
"But you may not want to apply any of these settings to your native Python "
"virtual environment."
msgstr ""
